	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Merging roms and screenshots into a single franken file?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Would it be hard to Frankenstein a two 2 in 1 screenshot image file with an embedded rom?<br /><br />So if you load it on a web site, or in a picture viewer, just the image would show, like a normal PNG.<br /><br />But when you load it in an emulator, the embedded rom plays? No nefarious reason i ask, totally not.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Dwedit</b> [ Wed Sep 06, 2017 9:23 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Merging roms and screenshots into a single franken file?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can do it with PDF files, since they will look for the PDF header after the NES header, as seen in <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?f=5&amp;t=16007" class="postlink">this thread</a>.<br />PNG files don't allow you to put in anything before the header, neither do JPEG files.  Although Irfanview will still view the images if there is garbage data before the image header, Google Chrome will not.<br />RAR files do allow you to put arbitrary data before the RAR header.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
